# GameNative — Game Compatibility & Max-FPS Guide

## Architecture Overview

```
KnownGameFixes     → per-game hardcoded fixes (always wins)
      ↓
GameConfigRecommender → hardware-based defaults for unrecognized games
      ↓
LaunchOrchestrator.applyGameConfig → writes env vars to Wine process
      ↓
LaunchOrchestrator.applyIsolationEnv → per-game cache paths + driver vars
```

**Priority rule**: `KnownGameFixes.extraEnvVars` **always** overrides everything.
Applied last via `envVars.put(key, value)` (not `putIfAbsent`) in `applyGameConfig`.

---

## Adding a New Game

Add an entry to the `fixes` map in `KnownGameFixes.kt`:

```kotlin
123456 to GameFix(
    appId = 123456,
    gameName = "Game Name",
    protonVersion = ProtonVersion.PROTON_9_0,   // omit to use recommender default
    dxVersion = DxVersion.DX11,                  // omit for AUTO detection
    resolutionScale = 0.75f,                     // omit for hardware-based default
    forceUseLegacyDrm = false,                   // true only for Aspyr/sub-launcher games
    gameExePath = "",                            // non-empty only when forceUseLegacyDrm=true
    extraEnvVars = mapOf(
        "DXVK_ASYNC" to "1",
        "DXVK_GPLASYNCCACHE" to "1",
    ),
    launchArgs = "",
    reason = "One sentence explaining why this fix is needed",
),
```

**Minimum viable fix for any unrecognized DX11 game** — just this gets it booting:
```kotlin
extraEnvVars = mapOf("DXVK_ASYNC" to "1", "DXVK_GPLASYNCCACHE" to "1")
```

