## Pattern Library by Engine / DX Version

### DX9 games (Source Engine, UE3, id Tech 4, old Aspyr ports)
```kotlin
dxVersion = DxVersion.DX9
extraEnvVars = mapOf(
    "DXVK_ASYNC" to "1",
    "DXVK_GPLASYNCCACHE" to "1",
    "WINEDLLOVERRIDES" to "mfplat.dll=n,b;xaudio2_7.dll=n,b",
    "PULSE_LATENCY_MSEC" to "60",
)
// If game shows "browse for file" dialog → set forceUseLegacyDrm=true + gameExePath
```

### DX11 games (UE4, CryEngine, id Tech 6, RE Engine, most modern indie)
```kotlin
dxVersion = DxVersion.DX11
protonVersion = ProtonVersion.PROTON_9_0  // 9.0 more stable than 10.0 for most DX11
extraEnvVars = mapOf(
    "DXVK_ASYNC" to "1",
    "DXVK_GPLASYNCCACHE" to "1",
)
// Games with video/intro hangs: add "WINEDLLOVERRIDES" to "mfplat.dll=n,b;xaudio2_7.dll=n,b"
```

### DX12 games (UE5, id Tech 7, late RE Engine, Sony first-party ports)
```kotlin
dxVersion = DxVersion.DX12
protonVersion = ProtonVersion.PROTON_9_0
resolutionScale = 0.75f  // DX12 is more GPU-hungry on Adreno
extraEnvVars = mapOf(
    // Pipeline library cache: CRITICAL for DX12 — prevents massive stutter on Adreno
    "VKD3D_CONFIG" to "pipeline_library_app_cache,no_upload_hvv,force_static_cbv",
    "PROTON_ENABLE_NVAPI" to "0",   // disable NVAPI — wastes CPU, no benefit on ARM
    "VKD3D_SHADER_MODEL" to "6_5", // Adreno 7xx supports 6_5 with Turnip
)
```

### Unity games (any DX version)
```kotlin
dxVersion = DxVersion.DX11  // Unity defaults to DX11 on Wine
extraEnvVars = mapOf("DXVK_ASYNC" to "1")
// Most Unity games are Platinum on ProtonDB — no special fixes needed
```

### .NET / XNA / FNA games (Stardew Valley, Celeste, Terraria)
```kotlin
protonVersion = ProtonVersion.PROTON_9_0
dxVersion = DxVersion.DX11
extraEnvVars = mapOf("DXVK_ASYNC" to "1")
// These run via Mono — very lightweight, excellent compatibility
```

